  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the woman took and spread a covering over the well's mouth,.... This woman, very probably, was the man's wife of the house, as Abarbinel notes; who took a cloth, and spread it over the well's mouth, that it could not be seen or known that there was a well there: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and spread ground corn thereon: just taken out of the mill, before it was sifted, while in the bran; or corn unhusked, or just threshed out, in order to be dried in the sun, and then parched; or wheat bruised for that purpose: Josephus says (q) they were locks of wool she spread: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the thing was not known; that the young men were in the well. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(q) Antiqu. l. 7. c. 9. sect. 7. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(q) Antiqu. l. 7. c. 9. sect. 7. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
